1 (i) Originated from the bank;
2 (ii) Originated from someone affiliated, connected, or associated
3 with the bank;
4 (iii) Is approved or sponsored by the bank; or
5 (iv) Is the responsibility of the bank.
6 (c) In addition to any other remedies a bank may have under any other provision
7 of law, a bank that is affected by a violation of subsection (b) of this section may bring an
8 action against the person that committed the violation to recover:
9 (1) Actual damages sustained as a result of the violation;
10 (2) Either:
11 (i) All profits attributable to the violation; or
12 (ii) $1,000 for each violation; and
13 (3) Court costs and reasonable attorney’s fees.
14 (d) Any person who violates subsection (a) of this section is guilty of a
15 misdemeanor and on conviction is subject to a fine not exceeding $3,000 or imprisonment
16 not exceeding 5 years or both.
